      "text": "Intriguing artefacts are emerging out of our experimenting. We’re gauging an impact on class culture, learning through a DIG is changing the way learners interact with each other. Our teachers speak of learning communities empowered by higher levels of trust and connection. They’re noticing that their learners are more willing to take risks, to be vulnerable and uncomfortable in their learning. There’s a shift in their courage and confidence. Levels of engagement have changed profoundly for individuals. "
